title: Wednesday’s Advocate High School Roundup
text:
Wednesday’s Advocate High School Roundup Published 10:23 pm, Wednesday, October 7, 2015 
Izzy Taylor , Kitty Crosby and Sami Huff led the way as the Darien High School girls volleyball team improved to 8-0 Wednesday by downing Warde, 3-0. 
GIRLS VOLLEYBALL 
McMAHON 3, TRINITY CATHOLIC 0 
McMAHON 
15 8 17— 0 
Records: McMahon (8-2, 5-2 League); Trinity Catholic (8-2, 4-2 League) 
Highlights: McM — MeredithPellegrino had 15 service points, 2 aces, 19 kills, 12 digs, 2 blocks. Taylor Morton had 20 service points, 2 aces, 15 kills, 10 digs, 3 blocks. Molly Fusarelli had 19 service points, 6 aces, 3 kills, 2 digs, 35 assists. Tes DeJaeger had 10 service points, 4 aces, 16 digs. McMahon qualified for state playoffs. 
TC — Riley Griffin 6 service points, 2 aces, 1 kill, 3 blocks, 9 digs. Leah Zarrilli 4 service points, 1 ace, 2 kills, 12 assists. Elle Smyth 6 kills, 7 digs.
